<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-507-113  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 507 113.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>PC Week  Oct 15 1990 v7 n41 p19(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Airis adds video output to list of features in VH-286 laptop.andO;(Airis Computer Corp. VH-286) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brennan, Laura.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Airis Computer Corp. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Airis Computer VH-286 (Portable computer) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Laptop computersProduct Introduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>By Laura BrennanandM;Airis Computer Corp. has added video output to its much-anticipated notebookPC, now set for delivery next month.andM;The $1,899 VH-286 laptop, originally planned for shipment last month, offersa wealth of components at an affordable price, analysts said.andM;The 6.5-pound PC sports a 12.5MHz 286 processor, 2M bytes of memory, a20M-byte hard drive, a 256K-byte cache, a backlit VGA display, a 2,400-bpsmodem, MS-DOS and LapLink software.andP;  The laptop runs for 12 hours on standardalkaline batteries and as many as eight hours on a rechargeable NiCad batterypack, company officials said.andM;The new video port lets users connect the laptop to standard VGA monitors,company officials said.andM;The VH-286's price should make it a hit in the notebook PC market, accordingto Peter Tiege, a senior analyst at market-research firm InfoCorp, inCupertino, Calif.andP;  &quot;Instead of going with off-the-shelf components, they'vedesigned it from the ground up, not only for user features, but formanufacturability,&quot; he said.andM;Airis, of Chicago, can be reached at (312) 384-5608.andO;</TEXT></DOC>